      "source": [
        "# Parkinson's Disease — Supervised Learning\n",
        "\n",
        "### Setup\n",
        "- **Training data**: D1 train set (from preprocessing Part 1)\n",
        "- **Validation data**: D1 test set (checks overfitting)\n",
        "- **Final test data**: D3 test set (cross-dataset generalization)\n",
        "- **Models**: Logistic Regression, KNN, Naive Bayes, Decision Tree, Random Forest, SVM, Gradient Boosting\n",
        "\n",
        "### Why this setup?\n",
        "D1 and D3 are both binary classification datasets with real Parkinson's/Healthy labels.\n",
        "Training on D1 and testing on D3 tests whether the model generalizes to unseen data from a different source.\n",
        "This is a stronger experiment than a simple train/test split on one dataset."
        # NOTE: Dataset 2 (Telemonitoring) is excluded from classification.
        # Reason: It contains continuous regression targets (motor_UPDRS, total_UPDRS)not a binary Parkinson's/Healthy label like D1 and D3.
        # Dataset 2 is used in the unsupervised notebook for clustering only.
